cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DM, cs.NE, cs.SI 

The paper discusses the use of genetic programming for evolving similarity functions for clustering, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data mining (cs.DM), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and social and information networks (cs.SI). However, since the paper focuses on the use of genetic programming, which is a type of evolutionary algorithm, cs.NE is more likely to be the second most relevant sub-category after cs.LG.
